(E'#SupportsInfo',E'default',E'&nbsp;\n\n[Society for the study of Evolution (SSE)](http://www.evolutionsociety.org) &nbsp; &nbsp; <img src="../static/images/logo_SSE.png" width="120px">\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n[Institut National de la Recherche Agronomique (INRA)](http://www.inra.fr)&nbsp; &nbsp; <img src="../static/images/INRA_logo.jpg" width="120px">\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n[Institut Sophia Agrobiotech (ISA)](http://www6.paca.inra.fr/institut-sophia-agrobiotech)&nbsp; &nbsp; <img src="../static/images/Institut_Sophia_Agrobiotech.jpg" width="120px">\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n[Centre pour la gestion et la biologie des populations (CBGP)](http://www6.montpellier.inra.fr/cbgp)&nbsp; &nbsp; <img src="../static/images/CBGP_inra_logo.png" width="120px">\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n[Labex TULIP](https://www.labex-tulip.fr)&nbsp; &nbsp; <img src="../static/images/LogoTULIPgrand.png" width="120px">\n\n&nbsp;\n\n[Labex CEMEB](http://www.labex-cemeb.org)&nbsp; &nbsp; <img src="../static/images/logo_cemeb_labex_centre_mediterraneen_environnement_et_biodiversite.gif" width="120px">\n&nbsp;\n\n[Sociedad Española de Biología Evolutiva](https://sesbe.org)&nbsp; &nbsp; <img src="../static/images/SESBE_logo.png" width="120px">'),
(E'#SupportsTitle',E'default',E''),
(E'#TemplateEmailForAuthorInfo',E'default',E'Dear AUTHOR,\n\nBla bla bla...'),
(E'#TemplateEmailForReviewInfo',E'default',E'If you want to suggest as a reviewer a person who is not member of {{description}}, you can use this template e-mail to send him/her a message.\n\n..................................\n\nDear XXX\n\nI’m writing you in my capacity as a recommender for the {{description}} ({{appname}}). I’m handling a paper preprint by XXX and entitled XXX (doi XXX).  \n\nI’m wondering if you would be willing to provide a review – possibly within 20 days – of the manuscript. If you are willing, please create an account on the website of {{appname}} (https://evolbiol.peercommunityin.org/). I can then send you a request for review through the website that will have to accept.  \n\nYou may not yet know about {{appname}}. Briefly, it is a community of researchers in Evolutionary Biology dedicated to reviewing and (if they are high quality) recommending articles publicly available in preprint servers (such as bioRxiv). Our motivation is to establishment a high-profile, free, public evaluation system for identifying high-quality articles. More information can be found on the web site, complete with a short video (https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jMhVl__gupg). Review itself works largely like it does for a journal (including the ability to remain anonymous or not, as you like).  \n\nLet me know if you think you can do the above review.  \nThanks in advance  \nBest wishes  \nXXX  \n\n..................................'),
(E'#TemplateEmailForReviewInfoTitle',E'default',NULL),
