(E'#UserAddSuggestedRecommender',E'default',E'You can suggest members of {{appname}} for considering your recommendation request. A member willing to consider your request becomes the “recommender” of your preprint and will evaluate it for a possible recommendation.'),
(E'#UserAddSuggestedRecommenderText',E'default',E'<div style="text-align: left;">\n<h3 style="text-align: center;"><strong>​​You need to suggest {{longname}} recommenders who could initiate the evaluation of your preprint. Five suggested recommenders is a sensible number. </strong></h3>\n<p>A recommender is very similar to a journal editor (responsible for finding reviewers, collecting reviews, and making editorial decisions based on reviews), and may eventually recommend your preprint after one or several rounds of review.</p>\n</div>\n<div style="text-align: left;">Please do not suggest recommenders for whom there might be a conflict of interest. {{longname}} recommenders are not allowed to handle preprints written by close colleagues (with whom they have published in the last four years, with whom they have received joint funding in the last four years, or with whom they are currently writing a manuscript, or submitting a grant proposal), or by family members, friends, or anyone for whom bias might affect the nature of the recommendation - see the <a title="code of ethical conduct" href="https://evolbiol.peercommunityin.org/about/ethics">code of conduct</a>\n<div style="text-align: left;"><span style="line-height: 1.2em;">&nbsp; </span></div>\n</div>'),
(E'#UserAddSuggestedRecommenderTitle',E'default',E'<p>Suggest recommenders</p>'),
